# Project: DocuVault
# AI Document Organizer — Email Attachment Extractor & Categorizer

## What this app does
This is a SaaS web application that connects to users' email inboxes (Gmail via Google OAuth, and later Outlook), scans new emails every few hours in the background, extracts any attachments (PDFs, Excel sheets, Word docs, images, etc.), uses AI to categorize them into folders (Receipts, Travel, Work, School, Contracts, Subscriptions, Tickets, Tourism, Medical, Other), generates a short AI summary of the email the document came from, and stores both the file and summary securely so the user can access their documents anytime — even offline.

## Core principles — always follow these
- Write production-grade, scalable code. This app will serve thousands of real users.
- Security and privacy are the highest priority. User email contents must NEVER be logged, stored in plaintext, or accessible to the app owner. Only extracted attachments and AI-generated summaries are stored.
- Always handle errors gracefully. Every API call, database query, and background job must have try/catch with meaningful error messages.
- Write clean, readable, well-commented code. Comment the "why", not the "what".
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or credentials. Always use environment variables.
- Always think about what happens at scale: 10,000 users, large file volumes, rate limits.
- Mobile-first responsive design on all UI components.
- Follow accessibility best practices (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, semantic HTML).

## Tech stack — never deviate from this without asking
- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ with App Router (not Pages Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript throughout — no plain JavaScript files
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules unless necessary
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL) — for user data, document metadata, categories, summaries
- **File Storage:** Supabase Storage — for the actual attachment files
- **Authentication:** Supabase Auth with Google OAuth
- **Email Integration:** Google Gmail API via OAuth 2.0 (later: Microsoft Graph API for Outlook)
- **AI/LLM:** Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-6) — for categorization and summarization
- **Background Jobs:** Supabase Edge Functions or pg_cron — for scheduled email scanning
- **Payments:** Stripe — subscription billing with usage-based storage tiers
- **Deployment:** Vercel
- **Email queue/retry logic:** Use Supabase queues or a simple retry table in Postgres

